ern times."],"a":"A","question_type":"assertion_reason","concept_id":"sociology::introducing_indian_society","trap_option":"C","strong_distractors":["B","D"],"why_not_textbook":"This question examines nuanced views on caste's relevance today.","why_cuet_level":"Tests understanding of social dynamics and critical evaluation of assertions.","distractor_rationale":{"A":"Highlights the dynamic nature of caste roles beyond rigid definitions.","B":"Overstates the current relevance of caste without acknowledging changes over time.","C":"Incorrectly suggests that caste has no relevance in contemporary society, which overlooks its persistence.","D":"Fails to connect the reason adequately with ongoing implications of caste."}},{"q":"Read the statements and choose the correct option: Statement I: Urbanization has led to greater social mobility in Indian society. Statement II: This mobility has uniformly benefited all social groups. Statement III: Urban environments create new opportunities for various communities. Which options are valid?","o":["I only","I and III only","II and III only","I, II and III"],"a":"B","question_type":"statement_based","concept_id":"sociology::introducing_indian_society","trap_option":"D","strong_distractors":["A","C"],"why_not_textbook":"Encourages analysis of urbanization's impacts across different communities.","why_cuet_level":"Promotes evaluation of differing outcomes from urbanization processes.","distractor_rationale":{"A":"Recognizes urbanization's role but misses out on community-specific benefits and limitations.","B":"Correctly identifies both social mobility and opportunities while acknowledging uneven benefits.","C":"Misrepresents mobility as universally beneficial, neglecting disparities among groups.","D":"Incorrectly implies all statements are valid, ignoring nuances in urbanization effects."}}]}
