 flaw.","Only III contains a flaw.","Both I and III contain flaws."],"a":"C","question_type":"comparison_based","concept_id":"sociology::mass_media_and_communications","trap_option":"A","strong_distractors":["B","D"],"why_not_textbook":"The flawed statement suggests that audience participation guarantees credibility, which is misleading.","why_cuet_level":"This question tests critical thinking regarding credibility in digital contexts.","distractor_rationale":{"A":"This option incorrectly identifies I as flawed when it accurately describes a trend.","B":"This option misinterprets the implications of diversity in news dissemination.","C":"This option correctly identifies the misconception about digital content credibility.","D":"This option mistakenly claims multiple flaws where only one exists."}},{"q":"A researcher claims that advertising through mass media has no effect on consumer behavior because it targets specific demographics. Which response offers a better sociological insight?","o":["Advertising can influence consumer choices across various demographics by creating brand loyalty regardless of targeting.","Targeting specific demographics ensures that advertising messages resonate more effectively with intended audiences, which can shape behavior.","Mass media advertising is primarily about brand awareness with little impact on actual purchasing decisions across demographics.","Consumer behavior is unaffected by advertising if individuals are already predisposed to certain brands."],"a":"B","question_type":"application_based","concept_id":"sociology::mass_media_and_communications","trap_option":"C","strong_distractors":["A","D"],"why_not_textbook":"The options fail to recognize how targeted advertising can still shape consumer preferences significantly.","why_cuet_level":"This question challenges assumptions about advertising effectiveness based on demographic targeting.","distractor_rationale":{"A":"This option overgeneralizes advertising effects without considering targeting nuances.","B":"This option accurately describes how targeted messaging can effectively shape consumer behavior.","C":"This option minimizes the potential impact of advertising on purchasing decisions too broadly.","D":"This option incorrectly assumes predisposition negates any influence from advertising."}}]}
